00:20:10,930 --> 00:20:14,670
我喜欢你的声音  道格  很安抚人心
I like the sound of your voice, Doug. It's so soothing.

351
00:20:14,830 --> 00:20:16,870
我以前从没想过这个
I never really thought about it before,

352
00:20:17,060 --> 00:20:20,390
但在这方面  你让我觉得像弗兰西斯
but in just this way, you remind me of Francis.

353
00:20:21,240 --> 00:20:24,830
我真正想念的  是他的声音
The one thing I really miss is his voice.

354
00:20:25,270 --> 00:20:27,380
那一直是我最喜欢他的地方
It was always my favorite thing about him.

355
00:20:28,280 --> 00:20:29,750
不管他说的是什么
No matter what he would say,

356
00:20:30,890 --> 00:20:33,040
他的声音让我觉得好像
the sound of his voice made me feel like

357
00:20:33,040 --> 00:20:35,010
一切都会没事
everything was going to be all right.

358
00:20:35,330 --> 00:20:36,250
不是的
It's not.

359
00:20:40,420 --> 00:20:42,580
除了安奈特  还有谁去了
Besides Annette, who else was there?

360
00:20:45,380 --> 00:20:48,270
只有我能救你  道格
I'm the only one who can save you, Doug.

361
00:20:48,460 --> 00:20:51,170
"他又问我是否不信上帝
"And then he asked if I had no faith in God.

362
00:20:51,240 --> 00:20:52,690
我说  你错了
I said, 'You have it wrong.

363
00:20:52,690 --> 00:20:54,640
是上帝不信我们"
It's God who has no faith in us.'"

364
00:20:54,640 --> 00:20:57,400
14分钟  要我给你放吗
Minute 14. Would you like me to play it for you?

365
00:20:57,730 --> 00:21:00,700
放弃调查  为你对他的抹黑道歉
Drop the investigation and apologize for what you're doing to him

366
00:21:00,700 --> 00:21:02,400
否则就会有更多泄露出来
or more of this is gonna come out.

367
00:21:02,770 --> 00:21:05,400
我要按播放了  我想要你听听
I'm gonna press play. I want you to hear it.

368
00:21:14,430 --> 00:21:17,420
{\an8}{\pos(54.9,51.4)}道·斯坦普

369
00:21:14,430 --> 00:21:17,420
{\an8}{\pos(48.9,92.3)}好梦

370
00:21:38,190 --> 00:21:40,200
我的安全团队刚告诉我
My security team just informed me

371
00:21:40,200 --> 00:21:44,260
俄罗斯士兵冲美军特种部队开枪了  维克多
that Russian soldiers are firing at American Special Forces, Viktor.

372
00:21:44,260 --> 00:21:45,640
是他们入侵了海岸
They invaded the coast,

373
00:21:45,700 --> 00:21:47,350
这违反了你我的协议
which violates agreements you and I made.

374
00:21:47,350 --> 00:21:49,770
是为了防止核装置
Preventing a nuclear device from--

375
00:21:49,770 --> 00:21:51,520
这是你策划的吗  克莱尔
Did you orchestrate this, Claire?

376
00:21:51,580 --> 00:21:54,660
为了什么  分散人们对你丈夫日记的注意
For what? To distract from your husband's diary?

377
00:21:54,660 --> 00:21:56,850
别装作你不会做出这种事
And don't act like that would be beneath you.

378
00:21:56,850 --> 00:22:01,030
我并不相信当母亲能自动让一个女人变成圣人
I don't believe motherhood automatically makes a woman a saint.

379
00:22:01,030 --> 00:22:03,100
-拉菲克·纳泽  -死了
- Rafiq Nasser-- - Is dead.

380
00:22:04,380 --> 00:22:06,460
我们一小时前用无人机袭击了他
We hit him with a drone strike an hour ago.

381
00:22:10,620 --> 00:22:13,540
他在给我们提供必要的情报
He was providing us with necessary intelligence.

382
00:22:13,550 --> 00:22:15,370
那是你先告诉他的
That you provided him with first.

383
00:22:15,380 --> 00:22:16,920
威胁是真的
The threat is real.

384
00:22:16,920 --> 00:22:19,590
我会让我格勒乌的人接手的
I'll have my people, the GRU, take it from here.

385
00:22:19,590 --> 00:22:20,790
不行
No, you won't.

386
00:22:20,790 --> 00:22:22,210
克莱尔
Look, Claire, just...

387
00:22:23,500 --> 00:22:25,720
专心生你的孩子去吧
worry about having your baby now.

388
00:22:29,150 --> 00:22:31,590
我一直觉得你的自大很好玩
I've always been entertained by your arrogance.

389
00:22:32,520 --> 00:22:35,760
就像是看已经过了时的电影
It's like watching some movie, just out of date.

390
00:22:38,510 --> 00:22:41,440
如果有危险分子拿到核武器  维克多
If a rogue element gets their hands on a nuclear device, Viktor,

391
00:22:41,440 --> 00:22:42,890
我会先出击的
I will strike first.

392
00:22:48,970 --> 00:22:51,450
你们那边现在几点
What time is it there now?

393
00:22:51,950 --> 00:22:54,150
快日出了吧
Must be close to sunrise, huh?

394
00:22:57,040 --> 00:22:58,000
快了
Just about.

395
00:23:03,700 --> 00:23:05,920
如果你丢原子弹
If you drop an atom bomb,

396
00:23:07,190 --> 00:23:09,250
我们的世界  你女儿的世界
our world, your daughter's world...

397
00:23:15,770 --> 00:23:18,710
太阳会永远变样的  克莱尔
That sun will never look the same again, Claire.

398
00:23:23,230 --> 00:23:24,650
你那边几点了
What time is it there?

399
00:23:32,710 --> 00:23:34,140
我正要吃午饭
I'm about to have lunch.

400
00:23:34,360 --> 00:23:35,670
你都吃什么
And what are you having?

401
00:23:36,800 --> 00:23:38,440
沙拉
Oh, a salad.

402
00:23:38,840 --> 00:23:41,460
黄瓜和西红柿  还有羊乳酪
Cucumbers and tomatoes, a bit of feta.

403
00:23:41,640 --> 00:23:45,280
西班牙橄榄  还有丹吉尔的草药
Some Spanish olive oil and herbs from Tangiers.

404
00:23:45,280 --> 00:23:47,360
我现在不吃面包了
I don't eat bread anymore, you know.

405
00:23:48,430 --> 00:23:50,950
我们还从未好好吃过一顿饭
We never had a proper meal, you and I.

406
00:23:52,260 --> 00:23:53,070
算不上吃过
Not really.

407
00:23:53,070 --> 00:23:56,270
我现在得在联合国公开反对你了
I'll have to oppose you now, openly at the UN.

408
00:23:56,920 --> 00:23:58,200
事事针对你
And at every turn.

409
00:24:00,880 --> 00:24:02,790
但私下里
Privately, I...

410
00:24:09,570 --> 00:24:10,720
我会想你的
I will miss you.

411
00:24:19,140 --> 00:24:21,300
我已跟佩特罗夫总统说明
As I made clear to President Petrov,

412
00:24:21,300 --> 00:24:24,780
我绝不会允许恐怖分子带着原子弹
I will not have terrorists waltzing out of the desert

413
00:24:24,790 --> 00:24:26,310
大摇大摆地走出沙漠
with an atomic bomb.

414
00:24:26,440 --> 00:24:29,810
我也该拿你们当大人了
It's time for me to treat you all like the adults you are.

415
00:24:30,720 --> 00:24:31,970
事实就是
The truth is...

416
00:24:32,890 --> 00:24:35,040
我不是唯一有危险的人
I'm not the only one who's in danger.

417
00:24:35,040 --> 00:24:38,290
没有人真正安全
No one's safe. Not really.

418
00:24:39,840 --> 00:24:40,680
永远都不
Not ever.

419
00:24:41,510 --> 00:24:45,020
那么会进行核打击吗  自长崎后的第一例
Does that mean a nuclear strike? The first one since Nagasaki?

420
00:24:45,270 --> 00:24:48,060
如果有必要的话  是的
If need be, yes.

421
00:24:50,290 --> 00:24:50,960
泰芮
Terry.

422
00:24:51,510 --> 00:24:53,720
你近来公开批评总统
You've become a vocal critic of the president.

423
00:24:53,720 --> 00:24:55,610
甚至在你被捕前
Even before your arrest.

424
00:24:55,610 --> 00:24:57,630
其实  你第一次公开露面
Actually, the first time you went public

425
00:24:57,630 --> 00:25:00,640
就是支持限制她权力的立法
was to support legislation limiting her powers.

426
00:25:00,640 --> 00:25:03,250
而现在这一点更加紧急了
Which is now more urgent than ever.

427
00:25:03,330 --> 00:25:04,860
最近  在你等待庭审时
And recently, as you await trial,

428
00:25:04,860 --> 00:25:07,510
又因为一些言论而陷入了更多麻烦
you got into some more hot water with your comments.

429
00:25:07,510 --> 00:25:09,480
是啊  我失言了
Yes, I misspoke.

430
00:25:09,760 --> 00:25:12,950
但说实话吧  这个总统简直要命
But let's face it. This president is fatal.

431
00:25:13,160 --> 00:25:16,590
她在刺激末日的到来
I mean, she's out there evoking end of days.

432
00:25:17,110 --> 00:25:18,340
她在任的话
And with her in office,

433
00:25:18,340 --> 00:25:20,900
国家就是会走向末日
that is exactly where this country is headed.

434
00:25:20,950 --> 00:25:22,270
我是什么
And what am I?

435
00:25:22,530 --> 00:25:27,300
因为我还相信家庭  就古板了吗
Some antiquated soul because I still believe in family?

436
00:25:27,930 --> 00:25:31,110
如果你想改变国家的贫困状态
Listen, if you want to do something in this country about poverty,

437
00:25:31,450 --> 00:25:32,420
就得靠家庭
family.

438
00:25:32,820 --> 00:25:35,280
减少犯罪  靠家庭
Crime, family.

439
00:25:35,750 --> 00:25:38,790
教育  靠家庭  家庭是一切
Education, family. It's family.

440
00:25:39,320 --> 00:25:42,830
我父母每晚都六点吃饭
My parents had dinner at six o'clock. Every single night.

441
00:25:42,830 --> 00:25:46,740
不管你在哪  在做什么
They didn't care where you were, what the hell you were doing.

442
00:25:46,740 --> 00:25:48,940
晚饭六点开始
Dinner was at six, goddamnit.

443
00:25:49,230 --> 00:25:52,410
你和你妹妹上一次一起吃晚饭是什么时候了
And when's the last time you and your sister had dinner?

444
00:25:57,620 --> 00:26:00,240
这个问题很合理
That is a fair question.

445
00:26:00,750 --> 00:26:03,180
我们的确
And it has been some time

446
00:26:03,320 --> 00:26:06,600
挺久没有面对面坐下来了
since we sat across from each other.

447
00:27:00,540 --> 00:27:01,500
你好吗  比尔
How you doing, Bill?

448
00:27:04,010 --> 00:27:05,460
看是哪天了
Depends on the day.

449
00:27:08,210 --> 00:27:09,350
还有用药剂量
And the dose.

450
00:27:14,530 --> 00:27:18,300
我给你带了点心来  乔治敦的普蓬
I brought you some pastries, from Poupon, Georgetown.

451
00:27:19,120 --> 00:27:20,760
我知道你就喜欢这个
I know you have a soft spot for those.

452
00:27:21,690 --> 00:27:23,630
我现在不吃糖了
Well, I don't do sugar anymore.

453
00:27:24,440 --> 00:27:27,380
只会助长肿瘤
It's... fuel for the tumor.

454
00:27:28,640 --> 00:27:30,090
你想吃的话吃一个吧
You can have one, if you want.

455
00:27:30,180 --> 00:27:31,450
不用了
No, I'm good.

456
00:27:34,960 --> 00:27:36,440
20年前
Twenty years ago,

457
00:27:37,310 --> 00:27:39,460
我大概会坐下来
I probably would have sat down...

458
00:27:40,650 --> 00:27:42,670
写本回忆录
and written out my memoirs,

459
00:27:44,200 --> 00:27:45,310
而不是
instead of...

460
00:27:46,670 --> 00:27:49,820
想尽办法把话说出去
trying to just get it out there any way I can.

461
00:27:54,650 --> 00:27:56,650
我以为她会来呢
I thought she would have come out.

462
00:28:00,170 --> 00:28:02,620
抱歉  她让我来了
I'm sorry. She sent me.

463
00:28:06,780 --> 00:28:08,340
她要我停下吗
Does she want me to stop?

464
00:28:10,410 --> 00:28:11,370
恰恰相反
The opposite.

465
00:28:12,550 --> 00:28:15,050
她要你继续猛烈抨击总统
She wants you to keep hitting the president hard...

466
00:28:16,800 --> 00:28:19,040
这样她就能出来反对你
so that she can come out against you.

467
00:28:23,620 --> 00:28:25,140
这会变得一团乱吗
Is this gonna be a mess?

468
00:28:29,390 --> 00:28:30,060
可能吧
Could be.

469
00:28:33,480 --> 00:28:34,860
什么时候变成这样的
When did it happen?

470
00:28:36,490 --> 00:28:38,670
我们成了拼命补救的一方
That we were the ones catching up.

471
00:28:41,810 --> 00:28:43,350
是我们没留神吗
Were we not paying attention?

472
00:28:45,180 --> 00:28:45,950
不够留神
Not enough.

473
00:28:47,630 --> 00:28:49,910
弗兰西斯就是个混蛋
Francis was a son of a bitch.

474
00:28:52,440 --> 00:28:55,440
但他是个厉害的混蛋
But he was a talented son of a bitch.

475
00:28:57,020 --> 00:28:58,800
他料到了她
He saw her coming.

476
00:29:00,510 --> 00:29:02,170
却阻止不了他自己
He just couldn't stop himself.

477
00:29:03,420 --> 00:29:04,390
或她
Or her.

478
00:29:07,610 --> 00:29:09,910
你觉得十年后我们会变成什么样  马克
Where do you think we're gonna be in ten years, Mark?

479
00:29:13,650 --> 00:29:15,510
拜托  这个问题我逢人便问
Come on. I'm asking everybody.

480
00:29:16,450 --> 00:29:19,260
-因为显而易见的原因  -你比我更常想这个
- For obvious reasons. - You think about it more than I do.

481
00:29:20,840 --> 00:29:23,330
大腹便便  醉眼迷离  心不在焉
Fat, wasted and distracted.

482
00:29:24,040 --> 00:29:27,180
这么过一晚还不错  但不能这么生活
Might be a good night out, but it's no way to live a life.

483
00:29:39,550 --> 00:29:42,090
拜托  十年后
Come on, ten years?

484
00:29:44,580 --> 00:29:45,330
我不知道
I don't know.

485
00:29:46,760 --> 00:29:48,720
事情并不会怎么改变  比尔
Things don't really change, Bill.

486
00:29:49,830 --> 00:29:50,530
只会...
They just--

487
00:29:51,990 --> 00:29:53,580
只会逐渐消逝  兄弟
They just fade away, man.

488
00:30:03,800 --> 00:30:05,050
天啊  我真愤怒
God, I'm angry.

489
00:30:12,610 --> 00:30:14,530
我听了你丈夫的录音
I heard your husband's voice.

490
00:30:15,560 --> 00:30:17,430
道格拉斯·斯坦普来找我们
Douglas Stamper came to us.

491
00:30:17,890 --> 00:30:20,360
要把弗兰西斯的日记给我们
Offered up Francis' diaries,

492
00:30:21,200 --> 00:30:24,210
道格给我放了部分片段
snippets of which Doug played for me.

493
00:30:26,610 --> 00:30:30,000
说实话  我想过拿它对付你
And to tell you the truth, I considered using it against you.

494
00:30:30,000 --> 00:30:31,900
但我觉得录音
But I don't think it should

495
00:30:31,900 --> 00:30:34,160
不应该被公开
ever find its way into the public sphere.

496
00:30:35,110 --> 00:30:37,940
-我很惊讶  -我不是我哥哥
- Forgive my surprise. - I'm not my brother.

497
00:30:38,120 --> 00:30:40,370
比尔现在对民主是不利的
Bill's become bad for democracy.

498
00:30:40,690 --> 00:30:41,940
和之前的弗兰西斯一样
Like Francis was.

499
00:30:42,720 --> 00:30:45,350
大家都喜欢看女生打架
The world loves a cat fight,

500
00:30:45,360 --> 00:30:48,560
但我说我们不要如他们的愿
but I say let's deny them the satisfaction.

501
00:30:49,270 --> 00:30:50,820
对我们来说还不算太迟
It's not too late for us.

502
00:30:52,980 --> 00:30:57,530
你说得对  我们不要让他们如愿
You know, you're right. Let's not give them what they want.

503
00:30:58,320 --> 00:30:59,380
去他们的
Fuck them all.

504
00:31:01,220 --> 00:31:02,570
抱歉  宝贝
Sorry, Angel.

505
00:31:03,990 --> 00:31:06,670
他们是能听到声音的  有这方面的研究
They hear things, you know. There have been studies.

506
00:31:07,170 --> 00:31:08,230
感觉是不是很棒
Is it amazing?

507
00:31:09,070 --> 00:31:09,870
是的
It is.

508
00:31:11,220 --> 00:31:12,870
她是个活泼的小东西
She's an active little thing.

509
00:31:14,510 --> 00:31:15,200
我可以摸摸吗
May I?

510
00:31:16,570 --> 00:31:17,300
当然可以
Sure.

511
00:31:24,890 --> 00:31:25,860
她在踢我
She's kicking.

512
00:31:32,950 --> 00:31:34,470
我们会解决掉道格的
We'll take care of Doug.

513
00:31:34,560 --> 00:31:37,360
我不相信你会支持我
I don't believe your support.

514
00:31:37,910 --> 00:31:39,860
你根本不会说谎  安妮
You're a bad liar, Annie.

515
00:31:40,820 --> 00:31:42,530
你还企图杀了她
And you tried to kill her.

516
00:31:42,530 --> 00:31:44,270
你手里有我儿子
You have my son.

517
00:31:44,270 --> 00:31:45,560
你准备怎么下手
How are you gonna do it?

518
00:31:46,590 --> 00:31:48,180
我不知道你在说什么
I don't know what you're talking about.

519
00:31:48,920 --> 00:31:51,660
告诉我其他人是谁  我就放了邓肯
Tell me who the others are and I will let Duncan go.

520
00:31:51,660 --> 00:31:55,030
-他是无辜的  和我一样  -天啊  得了
- He's innocent, as am I. - God, please.

521
00:31:55,030 --> 00:31:57,570
这所谓的核危机
This so-called nuclear crisis.

522
00:31:57,600 --> 00:31:59,250
你比弗兰克还糟糕
You're worse than Frank.

523
00:32:03,070 --> 00:32:04,380
她又在踢我了
She's kicking again.

524
00:32:07,620 --> 00:32:10,660
像是她感觉到  结局就快到了
It's like she senses we're nearing the end.

525
00:32:17,040 --> 00:32:18,970
唯一的问题是  道格
The only question, Doug, is

526
00:32:18,970 --> 00:32:21,770
如果你是他们的A计划  那他们的B计划是什么
if you're their plan A, what's their plan B?

527
00:32:22,270 --> 00:32:24,040
如果弗兰西斯还在  我们就能知道
If Francis were here, we'd know.

528
00:32:24,250 --> 00:32:25,940
是啊  如果他准备杀我
Yes. Well, if he was going to kill me,

529
00:32:25,940 --> 00:32:28,640
-他会怎么做  -他会利用你提供的机会
- how would he do it? - He'd find an opportunity you provided.

530
00:32:28,780 --> 00:32:31,600
他总是抢先人三步  是吧
He was always three steps ahead, wasn't he?

531
00:32:31,600 --> 00:32:32,800
弗兰西斯·安德伍德...
Francis Underwood...

